  "text": "Here we use E(y) and D(y) to respectively refer to the set of spines and dependencies in y. The function e maps a sentence x paired with a spine i, η to a feature vector. The function d maps dependencies within y to feature vectors. This decomposition is similar to the first-order model of [CITATION_1] , but with the addition of the e features.",
